ahInterface.name: ahInterface
ahInterface.description: This module contains the MIB definition of interface related information.

AhAuthenticationMethod.name: AhAuthenticationMethod
AhAuthenticationMethod.description: Authentication method supported within Aerohive AP

AhEncrytionMethod.name: AhEncrytionMethod
AhEncrytionMethod.description: Encryption method supported within Aerohive AP

ahXIfTable.name: ahXIfTable
ahXIfTable.description: Table of all the Interface/SSID info not covered by the rfc 2863

ahIfName.name: ahIfName
ahIfName.description: Name - uniquely identifies an AP Interface.

ahSSIDName.name: ahSSIDName
ahSSIDName.description: Name - identifies a wireless interface with Access mode. If the interface is not a wireless interface with Access mode, the SSIDName should be set N/A

ahIfPromiscuous.name: ahIfPromiscuous
ahIfPromiscuous.description: Indicates whether an interface is in promiscuous mode or not.

ahIfType.name: ahIfType
ahIfType.description: Indicates whether an interface is a physical or virtual one.

ahIfMode.name: ahIfMode
ahIfMode.description: Indicates whether an interface is used for Access or Backhaul currently.

ahIfConfMode.name: ahIfConfMode
ahIfConfMode.description: Indicates whether an interface is configured for Access or Backhaul.

ahClientIP.name: ahClientIP
ahClientIP.description: The IP address of the client if known. Otherwise, this field should be 0

ahClientHostname.name: ahClientHostname
ahClientHostname.description: The host name of the client if known. Otherwise, this field should be empty

ahClientRSSI.name: ahClientRSSI
ahClientRSSI.description: An indicator for the RSSI of the client derived from last communication

ahClientCWPUsed.description: The boolean indicating whether Captive Web Portal is used.
